About this item

  • The All-In-One Smart Family Calendar: Finally, a WiFi-connected digital calendar + planner touchscreen display that will get the whole family organized and running smoothly. It’s never been easier to keep the whole family informed by assigning each member their own color and chores. Your go-to wall calendar 2023-2024 and beyond.
  • Quick Set-Up: Simply plug it in, connect to Wi-Fi, and sync your calendars – all your events will automatically populate and sync. Add events or chores directly on the device or use the free to download mobile app. Compatible with Google Calendar, iCloud Calendar, Outlook Calendar, Cozi, and Yahoo.
  • Beautiful and Intuitive HD Smart Display: 15” touchscreen can be mounted on the wall or displayed on its stand. The wall mount or tabletop option make this the perfect daily planner for the home or work planner to add to your office.
  • Chore Chart and Meal Planning: Add, edit, and easily check off chores throughout the day. Encourage healthy habits and autonomy with the interactive Chore Chart that transforms routine tasks into rewarding accomplishments. Display your family's meal plan and never answer “what's for dinner?” again.
  • Download the Free App to Stay Informed From Anywhere: Access and manage everything on your Skylight Calendar through the mobile app. Add chores and tasks to the list on the go.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Mary Louise Churak
5.0 out of 5 stars Works great as a calendar and the other features are a nice bonus!
Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
Verified Purchase
I got a Skylight calendar to display my personal and business schedule in my living room. Syncing my Skylight with my Google calendar went smoothly once I figured out how much pressure it takes to use the touchscreen (ie a little more than on my phone.) I use the option to display a week at a time most often, but I noticed while I was on the phone with a client discussing an appointment that it's very easy to toggle to the month view, and it was helpful to do so without having to interrupt my call to look at the calendar on my phone. So the calendar function is great, but I've also been enjoying the other features. I wasn't actually sure I would use the photo screensaver, wondering if it would be too busy for my space. Once I adjusted the settings to make the display look good, I had fun choosing which pictures to upload. I used the chore chart feature to up a watering/feeding schedule for my plants without having to add reminders to my Google calendar that would clutter it. Again, I wasn't sure I would even use the chore chart feature, but once I got into setting it up, I realized how nice it is. My basil will be trimmed and fed on a schedule going forward! And that is the unlooked-for benefit of the Skylight Calendar, in my opinion: it looks wonderful, it has just enough features to be useful but not overwhelming, and it feels like I treated myself to something nice! At this point in my life, I am cautious about adding new devices or gadgets, especially screens, but this one is worth it. The Skylight Calendar doesn't solve a problem as such, but it makes things I do anyway easier and more graceful. It's one of those things that you buy and immediately wonder how you did things before. I put the calendar up on a wall with lots of prints and paintings, and despite being digital it looks like it belongs there. The photo screensaver is lovely to look at, and the calendar display is understated and easy to use. I would recommend this as a nice addition to your organizing tools or as a wonderful gift.

VM
5.0 out of 5 stars An Evolved Family Calendar
Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
Verified Purchase
The Skylight Calendar has changed the game for my family. Juggling work, family, and personal commitments is always a challenge, even with having a digital calendar in your pocket. My wife and I have had various shared calendars for awhile, but it's always been difficult to find the balance of what personal stuff needs to appear on what calendars and to avoid duplication of things. The Skylight Calendar has allowed us to finally stay organized and in sync with the various schedules that our family keeps, and displays it all in a visually and aesthetically pleasing way.

Setup is a breeze, and the Skylight syncs effortlessly and in real time with our digital calendars (it supports most major email platforms). The calendar is intuitive and easy to navigate, and can display all or specific calendars synced to it and has multiple customizable views. We have it set up in our kitchen, which all but ensures that everyone in my family, including those who care for our children during the week, are able to see what is on the agenda for the day, week, or month as well as any changes made to schedules in real time. It's also nice to be able to set an example for our children of being organized and having a schedule.

We've also taken to using a meal calendar that appears on our Skylight. The integrated lists feature is helpful when referencing what to make during a given week and what needs to be added to a grocery list. It's nice to have that all together, accessible by anyone in my family.

Overall, the Skylight Calendar is a great product for anyone - and especially families, in my case - who is looking for a way to stay organized and on track. It is easy to use, visually appealing, and packed with features. I highly recommend it.

3.0 out of 5 stars Unique wall planner!
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 31, 2024
Verified Purchase
We bought this with the intention of replacing the paper wall planner. It is a lot smaller, but A1 size touch screens are hard to come by. It connects to calendars very easily, and synchronises almost immediately. The entries are clear and easy to read and you can change the default settings. We use it in month mode, but a wall planner is usually 12 months on a single sheet, so this is not quite so easy. There is also no search feature - which is present on the calendars it connects to - and that is another frustration.
The advantage of this is that it connects to mobile calendars, which then makes the same diary entries visible in several places simultaneously. Making entries on the screen also synchronises immediately with cloud calendars. However we use it with Alexa, "Alexa, make an event for March 8th at 6pm", and Alexa will ask for other details. It then appears in this calendar immediately.
The unit is connected to several calendars, but we only use it with one displayed.
It is definitely not cheap (unless you buy it in USA and bring it back) but works very well, with a neat appearance.
